div.div: In this way you can assess with some degree of certainty which vector combination was causative of the output vector.

You have two possibilities, you know which degree of change is likely to answer the question of differentiating between the two possibilities, and you can measure the impact of change in one variable based on whether the new version of the prediction function varies too much from the other data & alternative possible states of the prediction function given common distortion functions, variable metadata, & data variance.

If you can't measure the impact of change (you don't have access to a simulation or observation environment), you can still apply the distortions and then check for compliance with types of prediction distortion patterns, distortion change patterns, variable patterns, etc.
